# Barba.js Conventions

## DOM Structure

Every page must include the barba wrapper and container:

```html
<body data-barba="wrapper">
  <nav><!-- persistent nav --></nav>
  <main data-barba="container" data-barba-namespace="page-name">
    <!-- page content that transitions -->
  </main>
  <footer><!-- persistent footer --></footer>
</body>
```

- The `wrapper` wraps the entire page and contains the `container`.
- Content outside the `container` persists across navigations (nav, footer).
- Content inside the `container` is replaced on each transition.
- Each page needs a unique `data-barba-namespace` value.

## Initialization

```typescript
import barba from '@barba/core';

barba.init({
  transitions: [{
    name: 'default',
    leave(data) { /* animate out data.current.container */ },
    enter(data) { /* animate in data.next.container */ },
  }],
});
```

## Lifecycle Hooks (in order)

1. `beforeAppear` / `appear` / `afterAppear` -- first page load
2. `before` -- transition starts
3. `beforeLeave` / `leave` / `afterLeave` -- old page exits
4. `beforeEnter` / `enter` / `afterEnter` -- new page enters
5. `after` -- transition ends

Use `leave` and `enter` for animations. Use `beforeEnter` to set up page-specific JS.

## Transitions

- Return a `Promise` or use `async/await` from `leave`/`enter` so barba waits for completion.
- Use `data.current.container` and `data.next.container` to target elements.
- Use transition rules (`to`, `from`, `namespace`) to scope transitions to specific pages.

```typescript
barba.init({
  transitions: [{
    name: 'home-fade',
    to: { namespace: ['home'] },
    leave: async (data) => fadeOut(data.current.container),
    enter: async (data) => fadeIn(data.next.container),
  }],
});
```

## Views

Use views for page-specific logic that runs on enter/leave:

```typescript
barba.init({
  views: [{
    namespace: 'home',
    beforeEnter() { /* init home-specific JS */ },
    afterLeave() { /* cleanup */ },
  }],
});
```

## Plugins

- `@barba/prefetch` -- prefetches links on hover for faster transitions
- `@barba/css` -- enables CSS-class-based transitions without JS animation code

## Common Pitfalls

- Always re-init page-specific scripts in `beforeEnter` or `afterEnter` since the DOM is replaced.
- Avoid `document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', ...)` for per-page logic; use barba hooks instead.
- Ensure all internal links are standard `<a href="...">` tags (no `target="_blank"` for internal routes).
